nth%20because%20its%20fast-growing%20trade%20started%20to%20flow%20elsewhere.%20Shipments%20fell%2016%25%20in%20June%20despite%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trade-deal-agreement-slash-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrade%20truce%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20two%20economic%20giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20China's%20exports%20to%20the%20world%20grew%205.9%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20defying%20expectations%20of%20a%20broad%20slowdown.%20Growth%20came%20from%20trade%20with%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20the%20EU%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20and%20India%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20analysis%20from%20ING.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EING%20isn't%20the%20only%20one%20seeing%20the%20trend.%20In%20a%20Monday%20note%2C%20analysts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20wrote%20that%20China's%20exports%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bresilient%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20part%20thanks%20to%20trade%20rerouting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Goldman%20Sachs%20analysts%20wrote%20that%20part%20of%20China's%20export%20resilience%20stems%20from%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fluidity%20of%20goods%20trade%20and%20Chinese%20exporters'%20ability%20to%20reroute%20trade%20flows.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20China's%20exports%20to%20the%20US%20declined%20by%20%2425.7%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20but%20this%20was%20more%20than%20fully%20offset%20by%20increased%20exports%20to%20other%20countries%2C%20resulting%20in%20growth%20of%205.9%25%20from%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20ING's%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcc87ccb-dea6-4c4f-a360-639228b682c8%5C%22%3EHigh-tech%20goods%20are%20driving%20China's%20exports%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20is%20particularly%20striking%20in%20high-tech%20and%20capital-intensive%20sectors.%20Exports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20lithium%20batteries%2C%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20and%20machine%20parts%20posted%20double-digit%20percentage%20point%20grow