i%3EVice%20President%20JD%20Vance%20spoke%20at%20an%20AI%20conference%20in%20DC%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20which%20also%20featured%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EVance%20argued%20AI's%20impact%20isn't%20fully%20reflected%20in%20current%20labor%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20criticized%20tech%20firms%20for%20relying%20on%20international%20talent%20instead%20of%20American%20STEM%20grads.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Winning%20the%20AI%20Race%20Summit%2C%20a%20conference%20hosted%20by%20venture%20capitalists%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Boptimistic%26quot%3B%20about%20artificial%20intelligence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-white-collar-jobs-outlook-dario-amodei-response-tech-leaders-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomating%20American%20jobs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVance%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20question%20asked%20by%20podcaster%20and%20tech%20investor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-the-world-of-angel-investor-jason-calacanis-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJason%20Calacanis%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20Trump%202.0%20is%20thinking%20about%20job%20displacement%20because%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20every%20self-driving%20car%20we%20put%20on%20the%20road%2C%20that's%20four%20drivers%20who%20are%20going%20to%20have%20their%20jobs%20retired%2C%26quot%3B%20Calacanis%2C%20an%20early%20Uber%20investor%2C%20added.%20%26quot%3BFor%20every%20Optimus%20robot%20or%20humanoid%20robot%20that%20eventually%20makes%20it%20into%20a%20factory%2C%20that'll%20be%20five%20or%20six%20factory%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVance%20seemed%20more%20bullish%20than%20alarmed%2C%20arguing%20that%20AI's%20impact%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20priced%20into%20the%20job%20market%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20robots%20were%20coming%20to%20take%20all%20of%20our%20jobs%2C%20you%20would%20see%20labor%20productivity%20skyrocketing%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20actually%2C%20you%20see%20labor%20productivity%20flatlining.%20What%20that%20means%2C%20actually%2C%20is%20that%20our%20country%20is%20under-indexed%20in%20technology%20and%20not%20over-indexed%20in%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanelists%2C%20including%20Vance%2C%20discussed%20how%20the%20US%20can%20dominate%20the%20AI%20race%20at%20Wednesday's%20who's%20who%20of%20venture%20capitalists%2C%20startup%20founders%2C%20and%20politicians.%20The%20topic%20has%20become%20an%20increasingly%20acute%20concern%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20as%20geopolitical%20tensions%20rise%2C%20following%20the%20release%20of%20Chinese%20AI%20startup%20DeepSeek's%20powerful%20R1%20model%20in%20January%2C%20which%20caught%20many%20investors%20and%20AI%20entrepreneurs%20by%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20other%20speakers%20at%20the%20event%20pitched%20AI%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20job%20creation.%20Chris%20Power%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20factory%20automation%20startup%20Hadrian%2C%20claimed%20that%20the%20company's%20new%20production%20facility%20in%20Arizona%20%E2%80%94%20expected%20to%20open%20in%20late%202025%20%E2%80%94%20could%20create%20over%20350%20new%20factory%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Vance%20expressed%20optimism%20about%20AI%20job%20automation%2C%20he%20criticized%20tech%20companies%20for%20their%20reliance%20on%20international%20labor.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20you%20see%20some%20Silicon%20Valley%20technology%20firms%2C%20especially%20the%20big%20firms%2C%20say%20that%20they%20are%20desperate%20for%20workers%20that%20they%20can't%20find%20%E2%80%94%20that%20they%20have%20to%20use%20overseas%20visa%20programs%20to%20find%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20yet%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20college-educated%20employment%20rate%20for%20STEM%20graduates%20in%20this%20country%20seems%20to%20be%20de