%5C%22%3ESubsidies%20expanded%20who%20was%20eligible%20for%20ACA%20health%20insurance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20GOP%20legislators%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaysandmeans.house.gov%2F2024%2F05%2F20%2Fchairmen-smith-arrington-request-budgetary-analysis-of-biden-plan-to-permanently-expand-obamacare-subsidies-for-the-wealthy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20policy%20expanded%20ACA%20eligibility%20too%20much%20and%20offered%20relief%20to%20higher%20earners%20while%20remaining%20costly%20to%20the%20country.%20A%20CBO%20projection%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2024-06%2F60437-Arrington-Smith-Letter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20making%20the%20policy%20permanent%20would%20increase%20the%20deficit%20by%20%24335%20billion%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20and%20reduce%20revenues%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20%2460%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20particularly%20concerning%20that%2C%20by%20removing%20the%20income%20eligibility%20limit%2C%20some%20of%20our%20nation's%20highest%20earners%20are%20now%20eligible%20for%20government%20assistance%2C%26quot%3B%20Reps.%20Jason%20Smith%20and%20Jodey%20Arrington%2C%20who%20respectively%20chair%20the%20House%20Ways%20and%20Means%20Committee%20and%20House%20Budget%20Committee%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbudget.house.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fcbo_joint_committee_on_taxation_letter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIn%20certain%20areas%20of%20the%20country%2C%20a%20family%20making%20as%20much%20as%20%24599%2C000%20in%202023%20could%20qualify%20for%20taxpayer-funded%20subsidies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20subsidies%2C%20only%20Americans%20earning%20between%20100%25%20and%20400%25%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faspe.hhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fdd73d4f00d8a819d10b2fdb70d254f7b%2Fdetailed-guidelines-2025.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E%20line%20qualified%2C%20or%20between%20%2415%2C650%20and%20%2462%2C600%20based%20on%20the%20current%20cutoff%20for%20a%20single%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20400%25%20limit%20was%20expanded%20under%20the%20new%20structure%2C%20meaning%20that%20some%20Americans%20with%20ACA%20coverage%20were%20newly%20eligible%20to%20have%20some%20premium%20relief%2C%20especially%20older%20beneficiaries.%20Those%20who%20made%20above%20the%20400%25%20line%2C%20but%20were%20spending%20over%208.5%25%20of%20their%20household%20income%20on%20premiums%2C%20became%20eligible%20for%20subsidies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristen%20Young%2C%20a%20visiting%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution's%20Center%20on%20Health%20Policy%2C%20said%20that%20those%20newly%20eligible%20Americans%20saw%20savings%20of%20around%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year%20on%20their%20premiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20people%20who%20are%20facing%20particularly%20large%20increases%20in%20premiums%20when%20these%20enhancements%20expire%2C%26quot%3B%20Young%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20KFF%20analysis%20found%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20Americans%20making%20%2440%2C000%2C%20or%20266%25%20of%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%2C%20could%20see%20their%20annual%20premiums%20increase%20by%20%241%2C247%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20take%20a%20single%20parent%20of%20one%20child%20earning%20%2450%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20that%20family%20is%20saving%20about%20%241%2C700%20because%20of%20the%20enhanced%20premiums.%20They're%20going%20to%20see%20their%20premium%20increase%20by%20about%2080%25%20next%20year%20when%20the%20subsidy%20enhancements%20go%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Young%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20family%20of%20four%20with%20a%20household%20income%20of%20%24130%2C000%2C%20they're%20saving%20%248%2C000%20a%20year%20with%20these%20enhancements%2C%20and%20they'll%20see%20their%20yearly%20premium%20increase%20by%20about%2060%20to%2070%25%20next%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d32d861b-ce1f-447c-a14c-823b58e6a636%5C%22%3EWhen%20health%20insurance%20costs%20go%20up%2C%20healthy%20young%20people%20tend%20to%20drop%20coverage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20expiration%20looming%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20and%20premiums%20expected%20to%20rise%2C%20many%20younger%20and%20healthier%20Americans%20may%20decide%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20coverage.%20This%20could%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20raise%20costs%20even%20more%20for%20those%20who%20remain%20on%20ACA%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20that%20younger%20and%20healthier%20group%2C%20it%20becomes%20more%20expensive%20to%20insure%20the%20remaining%20Americans%2C%20and%20costs%20go%20up%20across%20the%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20insurance%20companies%20correcting%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20people%20who%20are%20going%20to%20be%20enrolled%20in%20their%20plans%20will%20probably%20not%20be%20as%20healthy%2C%26quot%3B%20Yaver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20projection%20from%20the%20nonpartisan%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2025-06%2FWyden-Pallone-Neal_Letter_6-4-25.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20should%20the%20measures%20lapse%2C%204.2%20million%20more%20Americans%20would%20be%20uninsured%20by%202034.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20is%20really%20critical%20to%20health%20insurance%20is%20being%20able%20to%20essentially%20spread%20the%20risk%20of%20insuring%20people%20so%20that%20we%20can%20essentially%20bring%20younger%20and%20healthier%20people%20into%20the%20insured%20population%2C%26quot%3B%20Yaver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20Congress%20could%20step%20in%20and%20extend%20the%20subsidies%2C%20although%20that%20looks%20unlikely%2C%20as%20it%20would%20have%20to%20have%20bipartisan%20approval.%20The%20potential%