e-2-1753274662.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1753274662-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1753274662-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1753274662-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1753274662-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475136%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUsing%20cob%20as%20a%20building%20material%20eases%20the%20process%20of%20construction%20as%20the%20material%20is%20versatile%20to%20work%20with%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Cob%20is%20only%20as%20good%20as%20the%20soil%20from%20which%20the%20mud%20is%20sourced.%20So%2C%20Raghav%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CArchitects%20should%20ideally%20look%20for%20soil%20that%20has%20the%20right%20balance%20of%20clay%20and%20sand.%20Before%20building%20with%20mud%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20essential%20to%20test%20the%20soil.%20If%20the%20soil%20has%20too%20much%20clay%2C%20it%20may%20crack%20as%20it%20dries%3B%20adding%20sand%20helps%20balance%20that%20and%20improve%20workability.%20If%20it%E2%80%99s%20too%20sandy%2C%20the%20mix%20won%E2%80%99t%20hold%20together%20well%3B%20adding%20more%20clay%20brings%20cohesion%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20advises%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20layer%20thickness%20and%20drying%20times.%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F316563%2Ftamil-nadu-sustsainable-home-with-plastic-bottles-and-mud-chuzi-vinu-daniel%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMud%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20slower%2C%20seasonal%20process%20that%20calls%20for%20patience.%20It%20dries%20more%20slowly%20in%20winter%20compared%20to%20summer.%20Each%20layer%20needs%20time%20to%20dry%20and%20settle%20before%20the%20next%20is%20added.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Terracotta%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20biophilic%20design%20is%20what%20the%20architects%20at%20Venkataramanan%20Associates%20were%20going%20for%20when%20they%20designed%20The%20Earth%20Centre%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20a%20project%20developed%20and%20envisioned%20by%20Vista%20Spaces%2C%20using%20terracotta%20as%20the%20hero%20material.%20As%20architect%20Dhiraj%20Chilakapaty%20explains%2C%20the%20building%E2%80%99s%20envelope%20comprises%20three%20tiers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20structural%20blockwork%20base%2C%20an%20insulating%20air%20cavity%2C%20and%20an%20extruded%20terracotta%20cladding.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20layered%20wall%20system%20significantly%20improves%20thermal%20performance%2C%20reducing%20heat%20ingress%20and%20thereby%20lowering%20the%20building%E2%80%99s%20cooling%20demand%20by%20150%20tonnes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Vista%20Spaces%2C%20The%20Earth%20Centre%20reflects%20a%20forward-thinking%20approach%20to%20urban%20development%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20prioritises%20ecological%20performance%20and%20material%20sustainability%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Bengaluru%E2%80%99s%20built%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Earth%20Centre%20in%20Bengaluru%20is%20built%20using%20terracotta%20as%20the%20hero%20material%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fsustainable-architecture-1753275562-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475173%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Earth%20Centre%20in%20Bengaluru%20is%20built%20using%20terracotta%20as%20the%20hero%20material%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Venkataramanan%20Associates%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20the%20material%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETerracotta%20is%2C%20at%20its%20core%2C%20baked%20earth.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F361124%2Frammed-earth-timber-clay-sustainable-home-material-architecture-projects-in-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy-saving%20material%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20research%20suggests%2C%20elaborating%20that%20the%20firing%20process%20used%20in%20terracotta%20production%20typically%20requires%20lower%20temperatures%20compared%20to%20concrete%3B%20terracotta%20is%20also%20moisture-proof%3B%20it%20has%20good%20thermal%20and%20acoustic%20insulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20genius%20of%20the%20project%20lies%20in%20using%20terracotta%20not%20as%20a%20flat%20tile%20but%20as%20custom-moulded%20panels%20with%20a%20flared%20profile.%20This%20adds%20a%20bold%20dynamic%20to%20the%20construction.%20Elaborating%20on%20the%20design%2C%20Dhiraj%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CFifty%20percent%20of%20the%20terracotta%20used%20is%20recycled%2C%20making%20this%20one%20of%20the%20few%20buildings%20in%20Bengaluru%20to%20adopt%20such%20a%20high%20proportion%20